Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.00,0:00:08.00,forest title KB,,0,0,0,,FABLES \N of the\NGREEN FOREST
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.00,0:00:08.00,forest ep title C,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&HFFFFFF&}Today's episode:\N{\c&H25CE1D&}"The big boast"{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.80,0:00:31.07,forest lyrics C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is there anyone smarter than I?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.34,0:00:37.26,forest lyrics C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm the smartest one under the sky!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.10,0:00:40.47,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Good morning, Chatterer!\N- No matter when we meet,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.47,0:00:42.32,forest default C,,0,0,0,,you're always in good humour, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.02,0:00:46.86,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's for sure!\NI always have enough food...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.54,0:00:51.41,forest default C,,0,0,0,,...so I can do anything I wanna do,\Nany way I wanna do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.02,0:00:54.04,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Bragging again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.26,0:00:56.72,forest default C,,0,0,0,,But it's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.32,0:01:01.36,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Though I may not be very strong,\Nmy head is very sharp, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.53,0:01:05.57,forest default C,,0,0,0,,What I lack in strength, I can cover\Nmore than enough with my intelligence!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.79,0:01:07.32,forest default C,,0,0,0,,There's a lesson to be learned in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.95,0:01:09.12,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Oh?\N- Uh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.95,0:01:18.93,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Chatterer, let me ask you:\Ncompared to Sammy, who's smarter?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.49,0:01:23.71,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That guy? He doesn't even reach\Nthe bottom of my feet!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.10,0:01:28.09,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Smartness may be similar,\Nbut his is a crafty kind of smartness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.84,0:01:34.02,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, Chatterer, I'm gonna GET you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.56,0:01:42.43,forest default C,,0,0,0,,What are you planning to do, Sammy?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.00,0:01:47.44,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You'll see, you'll see. When I get through,\Nthere'll be no doubt as to who's smartest!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.78,0:01:51.74,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Do you mean to tell me, Sammy, that you're\Ngonna teach Chatterer a real good lesson?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.92,0:01:54.33,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Don't you think he's a little too smart for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.63,0:01:55.61,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.23,0:02:00.16,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I can think much smarter than him,\Nwith one wing right behind my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.23,0:02:04.40,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's our Sammy. A smart bird,\Nbut a little bit feather-brained!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.74,0:02:06.42,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Huh? Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.11,0:02:11.71,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Sammy, how are you going to trick Chatterer?\N- Yeah. Sammy, how are you going to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.22,0:02:16.13,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Never you mind. You will all find out\Njust as fast as Chatterer does.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.32,0:02:18.52,forest default C,,0,0,0,,And when he does, he'll be sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.52,0:02:37.26,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I just saw a weasel, just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.59,0:02:42.20,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I talked with him a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.47,0:02:45.64,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh?! W-w-where?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.98,0:02:50.17,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Oh, by your storeroom Number One.\N- Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.31,0:02:55.22,forest default C,,0,0,0,,On the outskirts of the forest. The weasel\Nsaid he's not leaving until he catches you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.60,0:02:59.42,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You didn't tell him that\NI was here, did you Sammy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.02,0:03:01.97,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Yeah, at least for the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.09,0:03:05.80,forest default C,,0,0,0,,But y-you're so conceited.\NSometimes I think that your type of guy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.90,0:03:08.79,forest default C,,0,0,0,,should better be caught\Nby a weasel, Chatterer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.12,0:03:13.51,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy, don't scare me like that!\NI beg you, please, don't tell the weasel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.44,0:03:18.16,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Then, will you listen to my request?\N- I'll listen to anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.72,0:03:20.83,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Well, then...\N- Well, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.34,0:03:24.12,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- As for my supper...\N- Your supper?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.50,0:03:29.26,forest default C,,0,0,0,,From today, for one week, every day, you will go\Nand get some corn for me from Mr. Brown's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.39,0:03:32.25,forest default C,,0,0,0,,From Mr. Brown's house?!\NOh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.18,0:03:39.49,forest default C,,0,0,0,,How about it? If you can promise me that,\NI won't tell the weasel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.02,0:03:41.66,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- That's ridiculous!\N- Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.02,0:03:45.44,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Because in the daytime,\NBlack the Cat and Bowser are on guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.33,0:03:48.37,forest default C,,0,0,0,,But you're real smart, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.06,0:03:50.50,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.84,0:03:55.60,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Then I would think it would be extremely simple\Nto fool Black's eyes, do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.60,0:03:57.20,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Okay, Sammy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.61,0:04:14.68,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be waiting here.\NSo hurry and go get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.37,0:04:17.98,forest default C,,0,0,0,,And please, make it the most\Ndelicious looking ones!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.53,0:04:31.36,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.24,0:04:50.86,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.97,0:05:00.78,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.55,0:05:08.17,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Ah! Ah! Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.45,0:05:21.03,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Blackie, you foolish black cat, yeah.\NYou can't even jump up till here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.74,0:05:45.48,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh... Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.05,0:05:47.77,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh... What a predicament!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.96,0:05:51.46,forest default C,,0,0,0,,It went smoothe today. But it doesn't mean\Ntomorrow will go smoothe too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.76,0:05:54.56,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh... Isn't there a good solution?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.81,0:05:59.50,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I could get the corn without\Ngoing to the corn field,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.90,0:06:01.50,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I wouldn't be chased by Black.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.78,0:06:06.73,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's it! Eureka, I've got it!\NYeah, Sammy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.33,0:06:10.49,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Too bad you're not gonna have\Nthe satisfaction of seeing me scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.82,0:06:12.76,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Gosh, I've got such a smart head!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.02,0:06:15.94,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I'm overwhelmed,\Neven if I do say so myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.30,0:06:24.72,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Today is another beautiful day!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.76,0:06:27.48,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Good, good! It sure is great to be alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.70,0:06:33.34,forest lyrics C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who's the smartest one under the sky?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.89,0:06:36.78,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Say. Say, Chatterer, tell us,\Nwhat did you think of?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.66,0:06:40.50,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You'll be surprised when\Nyou find out what I thought of!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.75,0:06:44.04,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Then you will find out\Nhow smart I really-really am!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.54,0:06:49.44,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Yeah-yeah-yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.07,0:06:52.95,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy, exactly how long\Nare you gonna keep me waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.99,0:06:57.64,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Unless you get here on time,\Nit's very awkward.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.08,0:07:01.86,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, somehow I didn't think\Nthat you'd be here so early.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:06.24,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I'm always an early riser!\NWell, I'll be running off!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.98,0:07:15.70,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's funny, he should be more hesitating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.40,0:07:19.76,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That Chatterer was enthousiastic.\NBut did he say something to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.47,0:07:23.36,forest default C,,0,0,0,,He would just smile and laugh,\Nand not say a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.74,0:07:25.99,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.59,0:07:35.74,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Aha!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.70,0:07:48.32,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That Chatterer, he's late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.52,0:07:54.41,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe he was caught\Nat Mr. Brown's house, Johnny?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.41,0:07:57.83,forest default C,,0,0,0,,In spite of that, he left here\Nfull of confidence, Polly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.64,0:08:00.57,forest default C,,0,0,0,,But there's always the unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.97,0:08:04.88,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Sammy's wrong in making\Nsuch unreasonable demands!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.11,0:08:08.93,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's not so.\NHe's run off quietly giving them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.37,0:08:11.65,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Oh...\N- Hm. Hey! Chatterer!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.21,0:08:22.84,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Sure took a lot of time...\N- Well, maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.58,0:08:26.70,forest default C,,0,0,0,,We were really worried whether you\Nhad been seen by Blackie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.04,0:08:30.96,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I'm not so stupid as to be caught by that guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.23,0:08:34.60,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- My, how disgusting!{\i}\N- But it's the thruth!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.01,0:08:38.80,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Still got any complaints, huh?\N{\i1}Here! Still got any complaints?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.17,0:08:43.65,forest default C,,0,0,0,,This corn today doesn't taste very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.49,0:08:48.44,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Is that so?\N- Did you really get this corn from Mr. Brown's shed?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.80,0:08:50.80,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh, uh-huh, from his fence storage!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.56,0:08:55.11,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Huh, a fence storage?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.68,0:08:58.88,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but it's still corn from Mr. Brown's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.63,0:09:03.96,forest default C,,0,0,0,,How's that? Can't you realize\Nhow smart I am, from all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.90,0:09:07.51,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, tomorrow I'll feast you again all you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.85,0:09:12.39,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm sure Chatterer intends to go to his\Nstorehouse Number Two, tomorrow again.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.79,0:09:13.92,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If he can't enter...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.18,0:09:20.03,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy, Chatterer was one step better than you.\NNow, why not end it altogether?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.50,0:09:24.41,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hm. Never happened.\NWho is the smarter, we'll know tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.77,0:09:31.80,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.48,0:09:44.64,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Have you thought of a way to cut him down?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.18,0:09:49.86,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm really gonna make him realize\Nthat he's not very smart, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.28,0:09:53.82,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Say, tell me. How are you going to get him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.30,0:09:56.25,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Get over here.\NGet over here, I'll tell ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.96,0:09:59.61,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Oh?!\N- Oh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.91,0:10:05.75,forest default C,,0,0,0,,So, that's how it will be.\NWell, see you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.44,0:10:16.54,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now, the next day, Chatterer set out\Nenthusiastically, for his storeroom in the fence.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.23,0:10:28.78,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.58,0:10:33.15,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.79,0:11:09.87,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.80,0:11:38.96,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Chatterer. Nothing happened, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.65,0:11:44.74,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hardly. Had a little excitement.\NBut it went fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.42,0:11:49.18,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hm. Liar. Look, you're still shaking like a leaf!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.39,0:11:53.47,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I am not shaking. I ran out of breath\Nand I haven't got it back, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.70,0:11:54.70,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Huh?\N- Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.50,0:12:00.08,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hm. You sure don't lark for words.\NHowever, you didn't bring the corn, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.72,0:12:01.55,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.75,0:12:04.93,forest default C,,0,0,0,,What? So you did run off scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.02,0:12:07.83,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well... I better have you hurry and go get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.00,0:12:09.45,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh... That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.26,0:12:12.81,forest default C,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to, that's fine.\NAs for promise...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.97,0:12:15.50,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- ...I'll just tell the weasel where your house is.\N- Ah...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.02,0:12:19.72,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I understand. As long as I go,\Nit's alright, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.66,0:12:25.94,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Again, Chatterer decided to go\Nto his storehouse by the fence.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.47,0:12:29.57,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But Whitetail was still guarding it,\Nso he couldn't get near.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.75,0:12:32.39,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.89,0:12:35.91,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.29,0:12:41.98,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Huh-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.46,0:12:45.68,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's strange.\NWhat's Whitetail doing over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.54,0:12:48.07,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- You failed, huh?{\i}\N- Oh...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.84,0:12:52.77,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm sorry to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.29,0:12:57.16,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Escaped you, huh?\N- I'm really sorry, specially since you told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.48,0:12:59.64,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Now, now, you needn't be so dejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.32,0:13:03.79,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy will probably be complaining.\NSo when he does, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.54,0:13:07.63,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- I'll rely on you.\N- I'll see you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.34,0:13:14.73,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh... So that's it! Sammy used Blacky\Nto tell Whitetail about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.49,0:13:17.60,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I'll definitely have my revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.99,0:13:20.52,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All day long,\NChatterer wondered and wondered...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.32,0:13:37.16,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How could he get even with Sammy?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.02,0:13:41.09,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Whitetail will probably be waiting\Nin an ambush tomorrow. With only Whitetail...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.43,0:13:42.92,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's it, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.84,0:13:46.94,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The very next day, Chatterer acted on his idea.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.60,0:13:50.52,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Right at daybreak, before anyone else was up...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.40,0:13:56.17,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...he went to Mr. Brown's corn storehouse...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.08,0:14:00.12,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...and followed his own secret way inside.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.49,0:14:07.28,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Once inside, he gathered some corn.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.26,0:14:17.43,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then he hid it in a safe place in the fence.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.34,0:14:21.46,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}By doing this, he felt\Nhe could give the corn to Sammy.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.18,0:14:24.34,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This plan went very smoothly.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.66,0:14:46.18,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, see ya, bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.42,0:14:52.68,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sammy, not knowing anything of the plan,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.89,0:14:56.94,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}didn't know what to make of this situation.\NHe got very discouraged.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.45,0:15:02.14,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.31,0:15:06.44,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Oh!\N- Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.78,0:15:16.53,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy, just because you can't cause any\Ntrouble, you don't have to make such a face!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.08,0:15:19.56,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm the smart one. To try and think\Nof getting me is a big mistake!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.28,0:15:23.73,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, till tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.02,0:15:36.19,forest default C,,0,0,0,,How mortifying! How mortifying!\NAs matters stand,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.43,0:15:40.27,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Chatterer will be considered\Nthe smarter one. How mortifying!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.02,0:15:45.12,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Isn't there something that I can do?\NHow mortifying! How mortifying!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.99,0:15:48.71,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Just a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.17,0:15:53.65,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That Chatterer, he'll probably go\Nagain to the stone fence for more.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.70,0:15:57.72,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}From the stone fence...\NIf Reddy leaps out...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.08,0:16:02.01,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Wow! Save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.09,0:16:03.74,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Reddy?\N- Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.02,0:16:08.05,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm thinking of telling Reddy\Nabout Chatterer...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.45,0:16:10.57,forest default C,,0,0,0,,...going to the stone fence for corn.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.79,0:16:14.54,forest default C,,0,0,0,,How about that, gang?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.93,0:16:16.31,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Isn't it a good idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.60,0:16:19.52,forest default C,,0,0,0,,When he sees Reddy the Fox hiding\Nin the stone fence,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.68,0:16:22.21,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Chatterer won't hide the corn\Nthere anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.59,0:16:26.36,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Then, even if unwilling, he'll have\Nto go to Brown's house for the corn,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.47,0:16:27.76,forest default C,,0,0,0,,you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.18,0:16:31.60,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy! You must stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.78,0:16:36.46,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's right. To let Reddy catch him,\Nnotwithstanding, is too pitiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.84,0:16:40.56,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Huh. You guys really, really,\Ndon't know me at all, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.18,0:16:42.00,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Oh...\N- Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.94,0:16:44.95,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I just want to scare Chatterer, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.22,0:16:49.21,forest default C,,0,0,0,,If Chatterer is really in danger,\NI'll raise a ruckus and let him know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.56,0:16:51.54,forest default C,,0,0,0,,So don't you worry, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.67,0:16:56.96,forest default C,,0,0,0,,How is that? No complaints now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:00.98,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You sure are a weird old thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.96,0:17:04.38,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.29,0:17:08.58,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Huh? If you yourself say so, no worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.00,0:17:18.64,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hm. This must be the place\Nthat Sammy spoke of, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.12,0:17:26.26,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm going!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.18,0:17:27.94,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.40,0:17:44.18,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Huh?\N- Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.74,0:17:45.50,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.06,0:17:49.30,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Thanks for waiting!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.12,0:17:58.94,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Now, don't be bad. Full eat up, eat up!\NIf you want more, I'll get more.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.67,0:18:02.62,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Thanks, but my stomach\Nis not feeling too good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.82,0:18:04.94,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Next time, I'll accept your treat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.11,0:18:09.77,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy, actually thinking\Nabout apologize to Reddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.00,0:18:13.62,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Possibly, nothing will clear your throat.\N- Chatterer, how did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.06,0:18:16.85,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Some things are very obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.14,0:18:20.80,forest default C,,0,0,0,,If you're going to think of some way to bother me,\Nyou better think of a way better than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.04,0:18:22.99,forest default C,,0,0,0,,because I figured out your plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.54,0:18:25.04,forest default C,,0,0,0,,This morning, I saw Reddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.52,0:18:29.67,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Reddy! There's no point in hiding\Nbecause I saw you this morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.84,0:18:33.36,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- You better hide better than that!\N- Huh? Darn.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.50,0:18:36.56,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hm, I'll remember you for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.88,0:18:44.56,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy, all the trouble you went through\Nto have Reddy waiting in an ambush...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.76,0:18:46.63,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry that I didn't fall for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.46,0:18:49.44,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hm. Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.32,0:18:51.02,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Huh?\N- Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.28,0:18:54.30,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Serves you right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.76,0:18:59.44,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Now, do you see why I say that there is\Nno one around with a better head than me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.10,0:19:02.33,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Are you sure of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.57,0:19:04.85,forest default C,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.59,0:19:06.36,forest default C,,0,0,0,,But Chatterer...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.89,0:19:10.41,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That the weasel was just looking for you,\Nthat was just talk on the part of Sammy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.41,0:19:11.65,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.24,0:19:12.94,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.53,0:19:17.86,forest default C,,0,0,0,,And you, swallowing that story!\NIt can't be said that your head is that good!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.15,0:19:19.18,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.06,0:19:24.16,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, Chatterer, you think you're smarter\Nthan Sammy and that you outwitted him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.16,0:19:26.78,forest default C,,0,0,0,,But when you were about\Nto be caught by Black the Cat,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.96,0:19:30.97,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy deliberately raised a ruckus\Nand distracted him, and helped to save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.43,0:19:33.05,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.29,0:19:36.57,forest default C,,0,0,0,,If you think that you were able\Nto escape on your own,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.57,0:19:39.16,forest default C,,0,0,0,,well, I don't think that's being smart!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.29,0:19:59.04,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Oh?\N- Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.13,0:20:12.59,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy doesn't stand out now,\Nafter all that big talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.97,0:20:19.38,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Bragging is the most useless act in the world.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.80,0:20:23.88,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Because of his bragging, Chatterer\Nran into many frightening happenings.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.23,0:20:25.94,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sammy also was humiliated.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.94,0:20:28.62,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hm, a person's nature\Nis hard to change, isn't it?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.07,0:20:33.75,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And the two, after this, will always, until\Nthe day they die, probably continue to brag.{\i}
